Pachyseius humeralis
Berlese, 1910: 255; 
Berlese 1913
: 81; 
Castagnoli and Pegazzano 1985
: 187 (in part).

Legs. Leg setation as previously described in the genus (
Masan 2007
), and for Pachyseius humeralis species group: tarsus IV bearing 17 setae (seta ad2 absent). Tarsus II with two obtuse spur-like distal setae pl1 and pl2 (Figure 5A).
